status: Indicates the technique used in creating motion in motion pictures or videorecordings.

definition (en): Animated films are produced using a variety of techniques including 1) cartoons; 2) graphic film (with paint or other media directly applied to the surface of the film); 3) model, clay, or puppet animation (where three-dimensional objects are photographed one frame at a time to achieve the effect of animation); and 4) other techniques.
Combination of animation and live action.
Item is not a motion picture or a videorecording.
Technique for creating motion is unknown.
Technique other than animation, animation and live action, live action.
